  "body": "go-ethereum version: 1.8\r\n\r\nCurrent the generated FooSession struct for a contract Foo uses completely pre-set call and transact options. However, a reasonable deadline of the context of a call/transact can only be decided at the call time.\r\n\r\nIt would be great if it allows setting a timeout explicit in a FooSession, which is used to calculate the deadline (by adding `time.Now()`) each time when sending an RPC request.",
